   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>C. The First Beast 1.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Corresponding to the Head of Gold</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>of the Great Human Image</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The first beast v. 4 corresponds to the head of gold of the great human image in 2:36-38, signifying Babylon with its founder and king Nebuchadnezzar.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>2.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Like a Lion</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The first beast was like a lion the king of the beasts, the most fierce and cruel.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>3.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Having the Wings of an Eagle</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The first beast also had the wings of an eagle.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The eagle is the king of the fowls.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The beast's eagle wings signify that it was in the air, which belongs to Satan, the ruler of the air, and that its move was swift.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>4.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Its Wings Being Plucked</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Daniel tells us that he watched until the wings of this beast were plucked.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>This plucking of its wings signifies that its moving power was taken away and that it became like a beast in the field, as mentioned in 4:23-25a.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>When God touched Nebuchadnezzar, he became like a beast in the field.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>5.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>Lifted Up from the Earth</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>and Made to Stand on Two Feet Like a Man</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>"It was lifted up from the earth and made to stand on two feet like a man; and a man's heart was given to it" 7:4b .</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>This means that it became like a man standing on the earth with a man's heart, as indicated in 4:25b, 32b.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>D. The Second Beast 1.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>Corresponding to the Breast</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>and Arms of Silver of the Great Human Image</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>The second beast 7:5 corresponds to the breast and arms of silver of the great human image in 2:32, 39a, signifying Medo-Persia.</S>
   </TEXT>
